    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-04-25T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-04-25T18:00:00-05:00" n="107"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d107">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/6601: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-25T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 25, 1934—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>30. Your 55, April 24, 2 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Forward full text by mail.<note n="53" xml:id="d107fn53">Not
                            printed.</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Department has declined to discuss or comment upon the statement issued by
                        the spokesman of the Japanese Foreign Office in regard to Japan’s attitude
                        toward China. Department desires that for the present American officials
                        withhold comment, awaiting developments. Without initiating any action
                        indicative of particular interest or concern, please report on reaction,
                        official and unofficial, and on developments.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Repeat paragraph 2 to Paris and Rome.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
